Funds managed by U.K. Unit trusts roseby 2.3 billion stg in February to stand at a record 37.2billion, the Unit Trust Association said.    By comparison, funds under management in January totalled34.9 billion stg and in February 1986, 22.9 billion.    The association statement said gross sales for Februaryrose 1.01 billion stg, the second consecutive month salesincreased over a billion stg. Gross sales in January totalled1.14 billion and 560.7 mln in February 1986.    The number of unit holder accounts rose by 93,000 to3,594,000, a rise of 36 pct during the last 12 months. REUTER&#3;